The paper deals with efficient algorithms for generating random graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of Metropolis Markov chains and binomial distribution sampling suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The focus on graph models and their generation algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
